HEADWORD: Plebs
<hw>Plebs</hw> <pr>(pl⟦ecr⟧bz)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. Cf.
<er>Plebe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The commonalty of ancient Rome
who were citizens without the usual political rights; the plebeians; --
distinguished from the <contr>patricians</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, the common people; the populace; -- construed
as a pl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plectile</ent>⟦br⟧
